<div id="review_731493941" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/731493941" />
    <a title="J. Kent Messum" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23165988-j-kent-messum"><img alt="J. Kent Messum" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442882127p2/23165988.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/731493941?book_show_action=true">Sep 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J. Kent Messum" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J. Kent Messum" href="/user/show/23165988-j-kent-messum">J. Kent Messum</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23165988-j-kent-messum?shelf=dangerous-writing">dangerous-writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23165988-j-kent-messum?shelf=ballsy">ballsy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer731493941" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17022263356347114072">I enjoyed this novel, though not as much as Sebold&apos;s &apos;The Lovely Bones&apos;. I didn&apos;t think it was stellar, but I thought it was solid. A lot of people took a massive shit on this book because they disliked Helen&apos;s character so much... but you know what? There are lots of ugly characters in the world, and they are far more believable than the fictional heroes and heroines we blindly champion because they offer us no incentive to wake up and smell the coffee. <br/><br/>I like REAL characters, offensive or othe</span>
  <span id="freeText17022263356347114072" style="display:none">I enjoyed this novel, though not as much as Sebold's 'The Lovely Bones'. I didn't think it was stellar, but I thought it was solid. A lot of people took a massive shit on this book because they disliked Helen's character so much... but you know what? There are lots of ugly characters in the world, and they are far more believable than the fictional heroes and heroines we blindly champion because they offer us no incentive to wake up and smell the coffee. <br /><br />I like REAL characters, offensive or otherwise, and Sebold definitely showed us the other side of what a protagonist in a novel can be. In fact, I surmise that Helen's character shares more in common with most people, much more than most people would ever want to admit. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17022263356347114072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


