<span id="freeTextContainer6902786698959880823">I can see why a lot of people do not like this book but I kind of get it. I mean if I had to live like she did, with a mother like that I would be bitter and a bit on the weird side too! I think she is a bit like a &quot;Wednesday Adams&quot; type character. A little dark and misunderstood. <br/>I actually liked the book, more than the rating lead me to believe that I would. I also coincidentally read it on #bellletstalk day for Mental Illness and it was quite fitting. <br/>Decent Read! <br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6902786698959880823" style="display:none">I can see why a lot of people do not like this book but I kind of get it. I mean if I had to live like she did, with a mother like that I would be bitter and a bit on the weird side too! I think she is a bit like a "Wednesday Adams" type character. A little dark and misunderstood. <br />I actually liked the book, more than the rating lead me to believe that I would. I also coincidentally read it on #bellletstalk day for Mental Illness and it was quite fitting. <br />Decent Read! <br /></span>
